# Sentinel environment variables
#
# ⚠️  SECURITY: Anything prefixed with VITE_ is bundled into the browser and
# publicly visible in the shipped JS. NEVER put a secret (API key, OAuth
# client secret, service-role key, Anthropic key) behind a VITE_ prefix.
# Secrets belong on the server only.

# --- Safe to expose (client-side, public by design) ---
# Supabase project URL and anon/public key are meant to be public; row-level
# security is what protects your data.
# VITE_SUPABASE_URL=https://your-project.supabase.co
# VITE_SUPABASE_ANON_KEY=your-anon-public-key

# --- Server-side only — do NOT prefix with VITE_, do NOT commit real values ---
# Used by backend / Supabase Edge Functions, never shipped to the browser:
# SUPABASE_SERVICE_ROLE_KEY=...
# GOOGLE_OAUTH_CLIENT_SECRET=...
# ANTHROPIC_API_KEY=sk-...
